									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 491 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='2 ratings - 3.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #020A0F;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												<DIV>Ok I posted an idea on the paladin boards but there not saying much. I would really like to hear what the warriors think of this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>Below is a post I did in repons to a thread but I would like some honest opinions from anyone that wants to give them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That aside let me toss out what I think a warrior should be. I will say right now that I have not played one above 20th so no I dont know the pain you guys have went through but this is EQ so I know it is or has been there. I do remember a not long ago time when I would OOC 50th paladin lfg and see at nearly the same time a warrior OOC 55th warrior lfg and I would get grab while he got to sit there and yes even then I thought that stank. So to a non warrior like me what should a warrior be. Below I will give my honest uneducated opinion so try not to hurt me to bad 
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Toughest guy in any room and I dont mean by&nbsp; a tiny amount. In equal level gear (what ever that is) he should beat a paladin or SK by 25% with both unbuffed. Now a paladin should be able to close that gap by about 5 to 10% buffed once both are raid buffed. Meaning both have the same cleric and shaman buffs then the paladin throws on his personal buffs. Now I am not saying the gap at that point should be 5 to 10%. I said closed by. In other words the gap drops to 15-20%.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. DPS. I think a warrior should beat a&nbsp;paladin by no less than 20% and should be no futher behind a monk than say 10% at most. Yes I did say that and I ment it. Warrior should be very close to monk DPS. Yes I have a post 50th monk. The monk has a number of other goodies. FD, mend, pulling. safefall...etc. Warrior aint got anything but his weapons. He paid dearly by giving up spells and I dang sure dont think he got what he paid for.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Taunt: Warrior taunt skill is flat not good enough. Disc and AAs should be used for emergency situations only! I think the warriors need a hugh increase in the taunt skill. How often it works and how much agro it does. I think a paladins taunt ability is just fine as is. The warrior should be useing nothing but his DPS and taunt button except when something bad happens. An unexpected add and he has to get snap agro before the cleric can buy the farm</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Mitigation: Again the warrior should lead the pack in this but here is where I expect to get blasted at. I believe the paladin should be extremly close. Say only 5% behind here. The warrior is still ahead through.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now stop and think about ALL the above. Feel free to give honest opinions. Warriors should have way more hitpoints than anyone. They should out taunt anyone (maybe by even double what they have now) with the taunt skill. There DPS should be very close to a monks and way better than paladins. As for the mitigation above. Hey, make me tougher and I will find a way to hold agro by GOD! I should have to use spells to hold the same agro level as a warrior. But dangit I clank just as much and smell like a iron factor just as much as a warrior does. I think a very good way for SOE to close the mitigation gap that has grown between the warrior and the knights is to FINALLY make shields worth useing. Give the paladins a shield disc very close in every way to warriors defense disc (like stone wall). Then give the wariors what they paid for (up there DPS, way up there taunt, increase there hitpoints!). I believe if SOE does that then warriors might not mind us paladins being able to get in a mobs face and stand toe to toe like them. Now guys before you go wild. Yes I just pulled those numbers above out my.... Try to respond to the spirit of this post. We have had enough of hair pulling here to last a life time LOL</DIV></DIV></DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
