						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>At 50th level, paladins and warriors pretty much tank identically, If any tank thats 55 is getting a group over a 50th tank, the reason is, they have 5 levels on you and just level alone makes a huge difference in tanking, especially if the mobs are above level 50.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Don't worry about "mitigation issues" for a long time to come, unless your planning on taking on mobs that hit for 3-7k anytime soon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warriors and paladins often complement each other in a group where a slower isn't available and the mobs are stunable, (or a slower is available and you need a stun to pull the mob off the slower temporarily) You should just tell the warrior what you are trying to do since you will pick up aggro chain stunning a mob, and he'll have to piggyback your aggro via taunt to get it off you.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another tip, instead of trying for a mad rush for level 70 and 700aa try to find people you enjoy playing with a make a list of them, make friends, thats what the game is really all about.</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
