												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
MichaelMac wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Toughest guy in any room&nbsp;... paladin should be able to close that gap by about 5 to 10% buffed&nbsp;... in other words the gap drops to 15-20%.</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2. DPS. I think a warrior should beat a&nbsp;paladin by no less than 20% and should be no futher behind a monk than say 10% at most.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3. Taunt: Warrior taunt skill is flat not good enough. Disc and AAs should be used for emergency situations only! I think the warriors need a hugh increase in the taunt skill. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4. Mitigation: Again the warrior should lead the pack in this but here is where I expect to get blasted at. I believe the paladin should be extremly close. Say only 5% behind here. The warrior is still ahead through.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></DIV></DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>1) 15-20 is too close.&nbsp; Warriors should have that margin (with identical gear) without a disc and should remain 50 percent with a disc.</P>
<P>2) I don't care about DPS.&nbsp; Give Knights more DPS than Warrior, it doesn't matter to me.</P>
<P>3) Taunt is all but useless.&nbsp; The success rate makes taunt not needed when it is successful and not helpful when it is needed.&nbsp; Success rates on deep reds and yellows needs to be significantly increased.</P>
<P>4) Warriors are far too close to Knights in mitigation today (with identical gear) and should be given better class gear or other solutions such as class based AC bonus percent.</P>
<P><BR>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
