						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>i'm a&nbsp; warrior .&nbsp; tried and&nbsp; true . level&nbsp; 65&nbsp; almost&nbsp; 300 aa later&nbsp; what&nbsp; is&nbsp; equal&nbsp; for&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; vs&nbsp; knights ?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>if&nbsp; you&nbsp; wanna&nbsp; be a knight&nbsp; ,&nbsp; be a&nbsp; knight&nbsp; .&nbsp;palidan&nbsp; are&nbsp; all lightweights . when&nbsp; was the last&nbsp; time&nbsp; you heard&nbsp; a&nbsp; fatty&nbsp; sk&nbsp; bitch&nbsp; about&nbsp; not&nbsp; being&nbsp; able&nbsp; to&nbsp; tank ?&nbsp; you&nbsp; don't&nbsp; . sk's&nbsp; know&nbsp; what they are .&nbsp; this&nbsp; thread&nbsp; is&nbsp; much&nbsp; too&nbsp; much&nbsp; knight (&nbsp; palidan )&nbsp; vs warrior&nbsp; issue&nbsp;, and&nbsp; it&nbsp; shouldn't&nbsp; be . </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>palidan&nbsp; get&nbsp; spells , sk&nbsp; get&nbsp; spells .&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; get&nbsp; defensive&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; and&nbsp; disciplines .&nbsp; seems&nbsp; pretty&nbsp; even&nbsp; to me&nbsp; so&nbsp; far&nbsp; . </DIV>
<DIV>pally&nbsp; use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp; sk use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ( at&nbsp; least&nbsp; in&nbsp; upper&nbsp; elemental&nbsp; because&nbsp; mobs&nbsp; riposte&nbsp; you&nbsp; for&nbsp; 2000 hp&nbsp; +&nbsp; )&nbsp; still&nbsp; seems&nbsp; even&nbsp; to me. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>now&nbsp; note ,&nbsp; i&nbsp; don't&nbsp; have&nbsp; elemental&nbsp; molds , but&nbsp; my&nbsp; gear&nbsp; is&nbsp; VT&nbsp; based (like all of my&nbsp; guild)&nbsp; what&nbsp; pally&nbsp; do&nbsp; have is&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp (from&nbsp; personal buff) and&nbsp; +- 100 ac&nbsp; compared&nbsp; to me . does it&nbsp; matter&nbsp; ?&nbsp; nope .&nbsp; so&nbsp; thats&nbsp; pretty&nbsp; even .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the&nbsp; 305 max&nbsp; melee stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; is&nbsp; all&nbsp; maxed&nbsp; anyway&nbsp; ,&nbsp; so&nbsp; no&nbsp; difference there .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>lets&nbsp; look&nbsp; at&nbsp; 1&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp;&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; get&nbsp; to&nbsp; dual&nbsp; wield&nbsp; but&nbsp; knights&nbsp; get&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; that&nbsp; have&nbsp; significantly&nbsp; better&nbsp; 1&nbsp; handed&nbsp; stats&nbsp; ,so&nbsp; dps&nbsp; is&nbsp; again&nbsp; about&nbsp; equal&nbsp; .warrior&nbsp; get&nbsp; a&nbsp; better&nbsp; selection&nbsp; of&nbsp; weapons ? umm&nbsp; boc&nbsp; ,&nbsp; bloodfrenzy&nbsp; , hategiver&nbsp; , hammer&nbsp; from&nbsp; xanamech , blade of&nbsp; war . or&nbsp; trash&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; .&nbsp;knights&nbsp; have&nbsp; some&nbsp; new toy&nbsp; from&nbsp; almost&nbsp; every&nbsp; zone&nbsp; post&nbsp; kunark&nbsp; that&nbsp; is&nbsp; better&nbsp; . but&nbsp; i'm&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; so&nbsp; lets&nbsp; call that&nbsp; equal .</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>are&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; equal&nbsp; ?&nbsp; yup&nbsp; .&nbsp; we&nbsp; are&nbsp; equal&nbsp; to&nbsp; the task (according&nbsp; to&nbsp; sony ) ,&nbsp; we&nbsp; have one&nbsp; job&nbsp;&nbsp;;&nbsp; in&nbsp; a group&nbsp; or in a&nbsp; raid&nbsp;, we&nbsp; eat the damage&nbsp; from&nbsp; the&nbsp; biggest&nbsp; baddest&nbsp; mob&nbsp; we&nbsp; can .&nbsp; do&nbsp; we&nbsp; have&nbsp; any other&nbsp; roles in a&nbsp; party&nbsp;or&nbsp; raid&nbsp;? nope ,&nbsp; absolutely&nbsp; not&nbsp; . can&nbsp; we&nbsp; solo&nbsp; for&nbsp; exp&nbsp;realistically&nbsp; with&nbsp; or&nbsp; without&nbsp; buffs ? nope . </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; do&nbsp; i&nbsp; want&nbsp; to&nbsp; see&nbsp; in&nbsp; the&nbsp; next&nbsp; expansion&nbsp; ?&nbsp; removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the statistic&nbsp; cap . give&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; an&nbsp; innate&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; to&nbsp; using&nbsp; items&nbsp; since&nbsp; thats&nbsp; what&nbsp; we&nbsp; do is use&nbsp; items , not&nbsp; use&nbsp; spells&nbsp; or&nbsp; other&nbsp; skills .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; changes&nbsp; do&nbsp; i think&nbsp; can&nbsp; be&nbsp; implemented&nbsp; immediatly&nbsp; for&nbsp; warrior without&nbsp; unbalancing&nbsp; ? make&nbsp; shield&nbsp; a&nbsp; greying&nbsp; ability&nbsp; , like&nbsp; taunt&nbsp; or&nbsp; kick&nbsp; or&nbsp; bash&nbsp; .&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i&nbsp; really&nbsp; don't&nbsp; see these&nbsp; requests&nbsp; as&nbsp; being&nbsp;&nbsp;unbalancing&nbsp;&nbsp;. unbuffed&nbsp; i&nbsp; have&nbsp; about&nbsp; 3600&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; and get&nbsp; about&nbsp; 5000&nbsp; from&nbsp; my&nbsp; gear&nbsp; and&nbsp; buffs . if&nbsp; you give&nbsp; warrior a&nbsp; 10 %&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; from&nbsp; gear&nbsp; that&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; about&nbsp; 50&nbsp; ac ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; stats&nbsp; that&nbsp; bounce&nbsp; off the stat cap .&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp&nbsp; is&nbsp; 1/4&nbsp; of&nbsp; one&nbsp; hit&nbsp; from&nbsp;&nbsp;plane of&nbsp; fire named .&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp; palidan&nbsp;personal&nbsp; buff is like&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp&nbsp; and&nbsp; 40&nbsp; ac .&nbsp; /shield&nbsp; is&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp; timed&nbsp; ability&nbsp; that&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; well&nbsp; documented .&nbsp;and&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; hotkeyable&nbsp; except&nbsp; by&nbsp;&nbsp;keyboard&nbsp; command .</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; makes&nbsp; a&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a&nbsp; gnome&nbsp; or&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; PRONOUNCED . it&nbsp; makes&nbsp; the&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a dark&nbsp; elf&nbsp; sk&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; sk&nbsp; mean&nbsp; something&nbsp; also .&nbsp;&nbsp;those&nbsp; are&nbsp; just&nbsp; exampes&nbsp; of&nbsp; in&nbsp; class&nbsp; differences ,&nbsp; lets&nbsp; look&nbsp; at&nbsp; a&nbsp; barbarian&nbsp; shaman&nbsp; vs&nbsp; a high elf&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; now .&nbsp; manapools&nbsp; will&nbsp; be&nbsp; extremely&nbsp; different&nbsp; depending&nbsp; on&nbsp; how&nbsp; you&nbsp; set&nbsp; your&nbsp; initial&nbsp; stats .&nbsp; canibalize&nbsp; will&nbsp; mean&nbsp; more&nbsp; and more .&nbsp; the spells&nbsp; they&nbsp; use&nbsp; per&nbsp; class&nbsp; would&nbsp; remain&nbsp; the same .&nbsp; how&nbsp; about&nbsp; a&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; ranger&nbsp; versus&nbsp; a&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; beastlord .&nbsp; obviously&nbsp; they&nbsp; get the same&nbsp; heal&nbsp; spells&nbsp;&nbsp; but&nbsp; the difference in&nbsp; manapool&nbsp; will&nbsp; make&nbsp; the&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; much&nbsp; more&nbsp; potent&nbsp; in&nbsp; that&nbsp; type&nbsp; auxillary&nbsp; role .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; do&nbsp; you think&nbsp; ?&nbsp; am&nbsp; i&nbsp; asking&nbsp; too much&nbsp; ?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
