						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR>
<DIV>i'm a&nbsp; warrior .&nbsp; tried and&nbsp; true . level&nbsp; 65&nbsp; almost&nbsp; 300 aa later&nbsp; what&nbsp; is&nbsp; equal&nbsp; for&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; vs&nbsp; knights ?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>if&nbsp; you&nbsp; wanna&nbsp; be a knight&nbsp; ,&nbsp; be a&nbsp; knight&nbsp; .&nbsp;palidan&nbsp; are&nbsp; all lightweights . when&nbsp; was the last&nbsp; time&nbsp; you heard&nbsp; a&nbsp; fatty&nbsp; sk&nbsp; bitch&nbsp; about&nbsp; not&nbsp; being&nbsp; able&nbsp; to&nbsp; tank ?&nbsp; you&nbsp; don't&nbsp; . sk's&nbsp; know&nbsp; what they are .&nbsp; this&nbsp; thread&nbsp; is&nbsp; much&nbsp; too&nbsp; much&nbsp; knight (&nbsp; palidan )&nbsp; vs warrior&nbsp; issue&nbsp;, and&nbsp; it&nbsp; shouldn't&nbsp; be . </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>palidan&nbsp; get&nbsp; spells , sk&nbsp; get&nbsp; spells .&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; get&nbsp; defensive&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; and&nbsp; disciplines .&nbsp; seems&nbsp; pretty&nbsp; even&nbsp; to me&nbsp; so&nbsp; far. </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Even with regard to overall class balance?&nbsp; Or even with regard to tanking abilities?&nbsp;</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>If you are talking overall class balance, there's definitely some "uneven" things between the 2 classes.&nbsp; It shows up pretty profoundly with raids being cancelled whenever Zero warriors are present.&nbsp; Ever see a raid cancelled when zero paladins or SKs are around?&nbsp; I haven't.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This isn't to say that the classes are wildly unbalanced.&nbsp; Just that "even-ness" isn't there like people want to believe.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>If you are talking tanking abilities, then I hope it&nbsp;is rather clear that warriors got the&nbsp;edge... as it should be.&nbsp; However, without the knights having a voidance discipline, the gap really is rather large.&nbsp; Too large, in fact.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do not claim it's too large for the purpose of bringing warriors down a peg.&nbsp; Rather, I say it to get knights up into the slot just below warriors on the tanking ladder.&nbsp; Yes, knights have better mitigation than rangers and monks, but without that voidance disc (which all other melees have), the "even-ness" (or "proper-ness" to use a more appropriate term) of knights and warriors is completely out the window.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>pally&nbsp; use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp; sk use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; use&nbsp; 2&nbsp; handers ( at&nbsp; least&nbsp; in&nbsp; upper&nbsp; elemental&nbsp; because&nbsp; mobs&nbsp; riposte&nbsp; you&nbsp; for&nbsp; 2000 hp&nbsp; +&nbsp; )&nbsp; still&nbsp; seems&nbsp; even&nbsp; to me. </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Holding a weapon, and being able to do something with it, are 2 different things.&nbsp; Knights (pre-OoW) max out&nbsp;on Offense skill at 225 and 2HS/2HB skill also at 225.&nbsp; This provides a much lesser attack rating.&nbsp; Combine this with lesser riposte, dodge, parry, chances to critical, etc, on top of using a different set of combat tables, and the&nbsp;knight DPS comes out about 20% below the warrior when holding the exact same 2-handed weapon.&nbsp; This is as it should be.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>now&nbsp; note ,&nbsp; i&nbsp; don't&nbsp; have&nbsp; elemental&nbsp; molds , but&nbsp; my&nbsp; gear&nbsp; is&nbsp; VT&nbsp; based (like all of my&nbsp; guild)&nbsp; what&nbsp; pally&nbsp; do&nbsp; have is&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp (from&nbsp; personal buff) and&nbsp; +- 100 ac&nbsp; compared&nbsp; to me . does it&nbsp; matter&nbsp; ?&nbsp; nope .&nbsp; so&nbsp; thats&nbsp; pretty&nbsp; even .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The extra HP from paladin self buffs becomes almost negligible when you get to the EP and Time gear.&nbsp; Fully EP geared paladins are looking at raid buffed numbers of 9k to 10k HP.&nbsp; Fully EP geared warriors are easily over 10, with 11k being rather common.&nbsp; That 1k HP may not sound like a lot, but trust me that it's huge.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The superior parry, riposted, and dodge skills, when combined with the warrior's 5% additional mitigation for the class, translates that "lowly" 1k of HP into something closer to 2-3k of difference between knights and warriors.&nbsp; Factor in the discipline Defensive and 3k suddenly jumps to 6k of difference.&nbsp; That's a full round of attacks from most boss mobs that the warrior just survived, but where the knight got splatted just like the int caster he was standing next to.&nbsp; And trust me when I say that for a plate wearing defensive melee class to crumple like an int caster... it's seriously disheartening.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the&nbsp; 305 max&nbsp; melee stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; is&nbsp; all&nbsp; maxed&nbsp; anyway&nbsp; ,&nbsp; so&nbsp; no&nbsp; difference there .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Priests and int casters have an AA skill to raise their wis/int cap to 355.&nbsp; I'm very surprised that the melee classes like warrior / rogue / monk do not have a corresponding skill to raise their str/sta to these same levels.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>lets&nbsp; look&nbsp; at&nbsp; 1&nbsp; handers ,&nbsp;&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; get&nbsp; to&nbsp; dual&nbsp; wield&nbsp; but&nbsp; knights&nbsp; get&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; that&nbsp; have&nbsp; significantly&nbsp; better&nbsp; 1&nbsp; handed&nbsp; stats&nbsp; ,so&nbsp; dps&nbsp; is&nbsp; again&nbsp; about&nbsp; equal&nbsp; .warrior&nbsp; get&nbsp; a&nbsp; better&nbsp; selection&nbsp; of&nbsp; weapons ? umm&nbsp; boc&nbsp; ,&nbsp; bloodfrenzy&nbsp; , hategiver&nbsp; , hammer&nbsp; from&nbsp; xanamech , blade of&nbsp; war . or&nbsp; trash&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; .&nbsp;knights&nbsp; have&nbsp; some&nbsp; new toy&nbsp; from&nbsp; almost&nbsp; every&nbsp; zone&nbsp; post&nbsp; kunark&nbsp; that&nbsp; is&nbsp; better&nbsp; . but&nbsp; i'm&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; so&nbsp; lets&nbsp; call that&nbsp; equal.</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This is some really bad misinformation.&nbsp; The better stats on knight 1-hand weapons is to keep the knights at the threshhold of 20% below warrior DPS.&nbsp; Remember, knights can't dual wield, so as the warriors pick up better weapons, the knights have to make up any lost ground&nbsp;with a single 1-handed weapon.&nbsp; Thus, knight 1-handers need to be slightly better damage-to-delay ratios than what warriors get just to maintain that 20% lower DPS.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>are&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; equal&nbsp; ?&nbsp; yup&nbsp; .&nbsp; we&nbsp; are&nbsp; equal&nbsp; to&nbsp; the task (according&nbsp; to&nbsp; sony ) ,&nbsp; we&nbsp; have one&nbsp; job&nbsp;&nbsp;;&nbsp; in&nbsp; a group&nbsp; or in a&nbsp; raid&nbsp;, we&nbsp; eat the damage&nbsp; from&nbsp; the&nbsp; biggest&nbsp; baddest&nbsp; mob&nbsp; we&nbsp; can .&nbsp; do&nbsp; we&nbsp; have&nbsp; any other&nbsp; roles in a&nbsp; party&nbsp;or&nbsp; raid&nbsp;? nope ,&nbsp; absolutely&nbsp; not&nbsp; . can&nbsp; we&nbsp; solo&nbsp; for&nbsp; exp&nbsp;realistically&nbsp; with&nbsp; or&nbsp; without&nbsp; buffs ? nope . </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Being able to solo with or without buffs is going way off target for the discussion.&nbsp; At higher levels (60+) very few classes can solo, and of the ones that can solo, all of them are caster classes, so it's irrelevent for discussions of knight vs. warrior disparities.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; do&nbsp; i&nbsp; want&nbsp; to&nbsp; see&nbsp; in&nbsp; the&nbsp; next&nbsp; expansion?&nbsp; removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the statistic&nbsp; cap . give&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; an&nbsp; innate&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; to&nbsp; using&nbsp; items&nbsp; since&nbsp; thats&nbsp; what&nbsp; we&nbsp; do is use&nbsp; items , not&nbsp; use&nbsp; spells&nbsp; or&nbsp; other&nbsp; skills.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>All classes use items.&nbsp; Melee classes are more dependent on gear, but I really can't see there being any logical reason for one class to get any bonus because of this.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; changes&nbsp; do&nbsp; i think&nbsp; can&nbsp; be&nbsp; implemented&nbsp; immediatly&nbsp; for&nbsp; warrior without&nbsp; unbalancing&nbsp; ? make&nbsp; shield&nbsp; a&nbsp; greying&nbsp; ability&nbsp; , like&nbsp; taunt&nbsp; or&nbsp; kick&nbsp; or&nbsp; bash.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Yeah, I can see this.&nbsp; Bringing the /shield ability into the forefront and making it much more part of the warrior profile seems logical.&nbsp; As it stands, I've seen this ability used by a player only once in all the time it's been in the game.&nbsp; NPCs use it far more often than players.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i&nbsp; really&nbsp; don't&nbsp; see these&nbsp; requests&nbsp; as&nbsp; being&nbsp;&nbsp;unbalancing&nbsp;&nbsp;. unbuffed&nbsp; i&nbsp; have&nbsp; about&nbsp; 3600&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; and get&nbsp; about&nbsp; 5000&nbsp; from&nbsp; my&nbsp; gear&nbsp; and&nbsp; buffs . if&nbsp; you give&nbsp; warrior a&nbsp; 10 %&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; from&nbsp; gear&nbsp; that&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; about&nbsp; 50&nbsp; ac ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; stats&nbsp; that&nbsp; bounce&nbsp; off the stat cap .&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp&nbsp; is&nbsp; 1/4&nbsp; of&nbsp; one&nbsp; hit&nbsp; from&nbsp;&nbsp;plane of&nbsp; fire named .&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp; palidan&nbsp;personal&nbsp; buff is like&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp&nbsp; and&nbsp; 40&nbsp; ac .&nbsp; /shield&nbsp; is&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp; timed&nbsp; ability&nbsp; that&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; well&nbsp; documented .&nbsp;and&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; hotkeyable&nbsp; except&nbsp; by&nbsp;&nbsp;keyboard&nbsp; command .</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>A level 65 warrior with 5k HP has a LOT of room for improvement in this game.&nbsp; The AA skills alone can easily add a good 2-3k to your HP total.&nbsp; Natural Durability, stamina boosts, sturdiness, etc, will boost your max HP significantly.&nbsp; Trying to justify an additional 10% on top of that while sitting in the middle to low ranges of the warrior numbers seems a bit overzealous.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; makes&nbsp; a&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a&nbsp; gnome&nbsp; or&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; PRONOUNCED. it&nbsp; makes&nbsp; the&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a dark&nbsp; elf&nbsp; sk&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; sk&nbsp; mean&nbsp; something&nbsp; also.&nbsp;&nbsp;those&nbsp; are&nbsp; just&nbsp; exampes&nbsp; of&nbsp; in&nbsp; class&nbsp; differences ,&nbsp; lets&nbsp; look&nbsp; at&nbsp; a&nbsp; barbarian&nbsp; shaman&nbsp; vs&nbsp; a high elf&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; now .&nbsp; manapools&nbsp; will&nbsp; be&nbsp; extremely&nbsp; different&nbsp; depending&nbsp; on&nbsp; how&nbsp; you&nbsp; set&nbsp; your&nbsp; initial&nbsp; stats .&nbsp; canibalize&nbsp; will&nbsp; mean&nbsp; more&nbsp; and more .&nbsp; the spells&nbsp; they&nbsp; use&nbsp; per&nbsp; class&nbsp; would&nbsp; remain&nbsp; the same .&nbsp; how&nbsp; about&nbsp; a&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; ranger&nbsp; versus&nbsp; a&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; beastlord .&nbsp; obviously&nbsp; they&nbsp; get the same&nbsp; heal&nbsp; spells&nbsp;&nbsp; but&nbsp; the difference in&nbsp; manapool&nbsp; will&nbsp; make&nbsp; the&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; much&nbsp; more&nbsp; potent&nbsp; in&nbsp; that&nbsp; type&nbsp; auxillary&nbsp; role .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This suggestion may seem like a good one at first, but examine what will really happen.&nbsp; Not only will warriors be the only tanks on raids, but now you are actually advocating that Ogre and Troll warriors be the only tanks by making racial differences at the low levels extend into the upper levels.&nbsp; By capping out the stats, all the races become equal and there's no preference for one race over another.&nbsp; At that point, it's gear and player ability that make a good tank what they are.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what&nbsp; do&nbsp; you think&nbsp; ?&nbsp; am&nbsp; i&nbsp; asking&nbsp; too much&nbsp; ?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
