						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>are&nbsp; you&nbsp; a&nbsp; pally&nbsp; or&nbsp; warrior lanceor ?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>palidan&nbsp; sk&nbsp; and&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; have&nbsp; different&nbsp; roles&nbsp; on&nbsp; raids .&nbsp; if&nbsp; their&nbsp; jobs&nbsp; were the same&nbsp; they&nbsp; would&nbsp; all&nbsp; have the same&nbsp; abilities . </DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>If you are talking tanking abilities, then I hope it&nbsp;is rather clear that warriors got the&nbsp;edge... as it should be.&nbsp; However, without the knights having a voidance discipline, the gap really is rather large.&nbsp; Too large, in fact.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do not claim it's too large for the purpose of bringing warriors down a peg.&nbsp; Rather, I say it to get knights up into the slot just below warriors on the tanking ladder.&nbsp; Yes, knights have better mitigation than rangers and monks, but without that voidance disc (which all other melees have), the "even-ness" (or "proper-ness" to use a more appropriate term) of knights and warriors is completely out the window.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>warrior&nbsp; are&nbsp; supposed&nbsp; to&nbsp; be&nbsp; superior in&nbsp; their&nbsp; role . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The superior parry, riposted, and dodge skills, when combined with the warrior's 5% additional mitigation for the class, translates that "lowly" 1k of HP into something closer to 2-3k of difference between knights and warriors.&nbsp; Factor in the discipline Defensive and 3k suddenly jumps to 6k of difference.&nbsp; That's a full round of attacks from most boss mobs that the warrior just survived, but where the knight got splatted just like the int caster he was standing next to.&nbsp; And trust me when I say that for a plate wearing defensive melee class to crumple like an int caster... it's seriously disheartening.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>umm&nbsp; isn't that&nbsp; what&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; are&nbsp; supposed&nbsp; to&nbsp; be ? are&nbsp; you&nbsp; arguing that&nbsp; silk&nbsp; wearers&nbsp; tank&nbsp; as&nbsp; well&nbsp; as&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; then&nbsp; ?&nbsp; maybe&nbsp; you&nbsp; should&nbsp; post that&nbsp; on&nbsp; the PALIDAN&nbsp; board .</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This is some really bad misinformation.&nbsp; The better stats on knight 1-hand weapons is to keep the knights at the threshhold of 20% below warrior DPS.&nbsp; Remember, knights can't dual wield, so as the warriors pick up better weapons, the knights have to make up any lost ground&nbsp;with a single 1-handed weapon.&nbsp; Thus, knight 1-handers need to be slightly better damage-to-delay ratios than what warriors get just to maintain that 20% lower DPS.&nbsp;</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>take&nbsp; into&nbsp; account&nbsp; how&nbsp; much&nbsp;&nbsp; undead&nbsp; there&nbsp; actually&nbsp; is . palidan actually&nbsp; out&nbsp; dps&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; take&nbsp; into&nbsp; account that&nbsp; when&nbsp; tanking&nbsp;&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; dualwielding&nbsp; is&nbsp; limited&nbsp; to&nbsp; the&nbsp; listed&nbsp; weapons . the&nbsp; original&nbsp; statement&nbsp; wat&nbsp; to&nbsp; show&nbsp; that the&nbsp; selection&nbsp; of&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; actually&nbsp; has&nbsp; to&nbsp; use&nbsp; is&nbsp; quite&nbsp; limited&nbsp; in&nbsp; relation&nbsp; to&nbsp; what&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; or&nbsp; sk can&nbsp; use&nbsp; to&nbsp; maintain&nbsp; the same&nbsp; job ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; about&nbsp; dps since&nbsp; dps&nbsp; doesn't&nbsp; make&nbsp; any&nbsp; difference&nbsp; toward&nbsp; actual&nbsp; aggro .&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Being able to solo with or without buffs is going way off target for the discussion.&nbsp; At higher levels (60+) very few classes can solo, and of the ones that can solo, all of them are caster classes, so it's irrelevent for discussions of knight vs. warrior disparities.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>the&nbsp; ability&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo&nbsp; for&nbsp; exp&nbsp; is&nbsp; totally&nbsp; relevant&nbsp; under&nbsp; every&nbsp; circumstance .&nbsp; only&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; and&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; cannot&nbsp; solo&nbsp; effectively&nbsp; somewhere&nbsp;&nbsp; post&nbsp; level&nbsp; 65&nbsp; . how&nbsp; much&nbsp; exp&nbsp; do&nbsp; you&nbsp; get while&nbsp; lfg&nbsp; ?&nbsp;&nbsp; how&nbsp; much&nbsp; can someone&nbsp; who&nbsp; can&nbsp; solo&nbsp; ?</DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV></DIV>
																		
