			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>
<DIV>i&nbsp; really&nbsp; don't&nbsp; see these&nbsp; requests&nbsp; as&nbsp; being&nbsp;&nbsp;unbalancing&nbsp;&nbsp;. unbuffed&nbsp; i&nbsp; have&nbsp; about&nbsp; 3600&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; and get&nbsp; about&nbsp; 5000&nbsp; from&nbsp; my&nbsp; gear&nbsp; and&nbsp; buffs . if&nbsp; you give&nbsp; warrior a&nbsp; 10 %&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; from&nbsp; gear&nbsp; that&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp ,&nbsp; about&nbsp; 50&nbsp; ac ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; stats&nbsp; that&nbsp; bounce&nbsp; off the stat cap .&nbsp; 500&nbsp; hp&nbsp; is&nbsp; 1/4&nbsp; of&nbsp; one&nbsp; hit&nbsp; from&nbsp;&nbsp;plane of&nbsp; fire named .&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp; palidan&nbsp;personal&nbsp; buff is like&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp&nbsp; and&nbsp; 40&nbsp; ac .&nbsp; /shield&nbsp; is&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp; timed&nbsp; ability&nbsp; that&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; well&nbsp; documented .&nbsp;and&nbsp; isn't&nbsp; hotkeyable&nbsp; except&nbsp; by&nbsp;&nbsp;keyboard&nbsp; command .</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>A level 65 warrior with 5k HP has a LOT of room for improvement in this game.&nbsp; The AA skills alone can easily add a good 2-3k to your HP total.&nbsp; Natural Durability, stamina boosts, sturdiness, etc, will boost your max HP significantly.&nbsp; Trying to justify an additional 10% on top of that while sitting in the middle to low ranges of the warrior numbers seems a bit overzealous.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>umm&nbsp; 3600&nbsp; nakid&nbsp; + 5000&nbsp; from&nbsp; gear&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp; 8600&nbsp; . remember&nbsp;&nbsp; that&nbsp;&nbsp; all&nbsp; plate&nbsp; classes&nbsp; at&nbsp; my&nbsp; level&nbsp; are&nbsp; using&nbsp; basically the&nbsp; same&nbsp; gear&nbsp; so&nbsp; the&nbsp; 400&nbsp; hp&nbsp; and&nbsp; 50&nbsp; ac&nbsp; from&nbsp; the palidan&nbsp; personal&nbsp; buff&nbsp; is&nbsp; significant&nbsp; ,&nbsp; its&nbsp; almost&nbsp; exactly&nbsp; what&nbsp; a&nbsp; 10 %&nbsp;&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; to&nbsp; equipment&nbsp; usage&nbsp; equals . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; makes&nbsp; a&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a&nbsp; gnome&nbsp; or&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; PRONOUNCED. it&nbsp; makes&nbsp; the&nbsp; difference&nbsp; between&nbsp; a dark&nbsp; elf&nbsp; sk&nbsp; and&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; sk&nbsp; mean&nbsp; something&nbsp; also.&nbsp;&nbsp;those&nbsp; are&nbsp; just&nbsp; exampes&nbsp; of&nbsp; in&nbsp; class&nbsp; differences ,&nbsp; lets&nbsp; look&nbsp; at&nbsp; a&nbsp; barbarian&nbsp; shaman&nbsp; vs&nbsp; a high elf&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; now .&nbsp; manapools&nbsp; will&nbsp; be&nbsp; extremely&nbsp; different&nbsp; depending&nbsp; on&nbsp; how&nbsp; you&nbsp; set&nbsp; your&nbsp; initial&nbsp; stats .&nbsp; canibalize&nbsp; will&nbsp; mean&nbsp; more&nbsp; and more .&nbsp; the spells&nbsp; they&nbsp; use&nbsp; per&nbsp; class&nbsp; would&nbsp; remain&nbsp; the same .&nbsp; how&nbsp; about&nbsp; a&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; ranger&nbsp; versus&nbsp; a&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; beastlord .&nbsp; obviously&nbsp; they&nbsp; get the same&nbsp; heal&nbsp; spells&nbsp;&nbsp; but&nbsp; the difference in&nbsp; manapool&nbsp; will&nbsp; make&nbsp; the&nbsp; halfling&nbsp; much&nbsp; more&nbsp; potent&nbsp; in&nbsp; that&nbsp; type&nbsp; auxillary&nbsp; role .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This suggestion may seem like a good one at first, but examine what will really happen.&nbsp; Not only will warriors be the only tanks on raids, but now you are actually advocating that Ogre and Troll warriors be the only tanks by making racial differences at the low levels extend into the upper levels.&nbsp; By capping out the stats, all the races become equal and there's no preference for one race over another.&nbsp; At that point, it's gear and player ability that make a good tank what they are.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>warriors&nbsp; are&nbsp; supposed&nbsp; to&nbsp; tank&nbsp; on&nbsp;&nbsp; raids&nbsp; ,&nbsp; thats our&nbsp; lot&nbsp; in&nbsp; life .&nbsp; i'm&nbsp; not&nbsp; advocating&nbsp;&nbsp; that&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; and&nbsp; trolls&nbsp; be&nbsp; the only tanks ,&nbsp; but&nbsp; ogre&nbsp; and&nbsp; troll&nbsp; pay&nbsp; a&nbsp; hefty&nbsp; penalty&nbsp; . removal&nbsp; of&nbsp; the stat&nbsp; cap&nbsp; will&nbsp; not&nbsp;&nbsp; remove&nbsp; exp penalty .&nbsp; it will however&nbsp; make&nbsp;differences&nbsp; in&nbsp; characters&nbsp; ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; the&nbsp; differences&nbsp; is&nbsp; what&nbsp; makes&nbsp; us&nbsp; interesting&nbsp; .&nbsp; not&nbsp; everyone&nbsp; does&nbsp; every&nbsp; encounter&nbsp; exactly&nbsp; the same ,&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; did ,&nbsp; why&nbsp; do it&nbsp; ?</FONT></DIV></DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
		<tr>

