						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
togam wrote:<BR>
<DIV>are&nbsp; you&nbsp; a&nbsp; pally&nbsp; or&nbsp; warrior lanceor ?</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>&lt;---------- Check the class symbol under the name.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>umm&nbsp; isn't that&nbsp; what&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; are&nbsp; supposed&nbsp; to&nbsp; be ? are&nbsp; you&nbsp; arguing that&nbsp; silk&nbsp; wearers&nbsp; tank&nbsp; as&nbsp; well&nbsp; as&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; then&nbsp; ?&nbsp; maybe&nbsp; you&nbsp; should&nbsp; post that&nbsp; on&nbsp; the PALIDAN&nbsp; board .</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>I'm saying that warrior skills and superior HP raise them above ALL classes, even the knights, as they currently are, and that an additional 10% bonus to the HP isn't needed because of the currently existing skills and such.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>No, I'm not saying that silk wearers tank as well as paladins.&nbsp; What I'm saying is that for extremely high damage output mobs, it doesn't matter if you are wearing silk and have 3000 hp, or wear plate and have 8000 hp.&nbsp; The mob will thrash you in one round either way if they are quad-hitting at 2500 each shot.&nbsp; At that point, the only survivors are the melee classes with their voidance discs activated.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The problem is that knights don't have a voidance disc.&nbsp; Thus, rangers, beastlords, berserkers, warriors, monks, rogues, and even bards survive, but paladins and shadow knights do not.&nbsp; So despite wearing plate armor, the knights die just like int casters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>This is some really bad misinformation.&nbsp; The better stats on knight 1-hand weapons is to keep the knights at the threshhold of 20% below warrior DPS.&nbsp; Remember, knights can't dual wield, so as the warriors pick up better weapons, the knights have to make up any lost ground&nbsp;with a single 1-handed weapon.&nbsp; Thus, knight 1-handers need to be slightly better damage-to-delay ratios than what warriors get just to maintain that 20% lower DPS.&nbsp;</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>take&nbsp; into&nbsp; account&nbsp; how&nbsp; much&nbsp;&nbsp; undead&nbsp; there&nbsp; actually&nbsp; is . palidan actually&nbsp; out&nbsp; dps&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; take&nbsp; into&nbsp; account that&nbsp; when&nbsp; tanking&nbsp;&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; dualwielding&nbsp; is&nbsp; limited&nbsp; to&nbsp; the&nbsp; listed&nbsp; weapons . the&nbsp; original&nbsp; statement&nbsp; wat&nbsp; to&nbsp; show&nbsp; that the&nbsp; selection&nbsp; of&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; actually&nbsp; has&nbsp; to&nbsp; use&nbsp; is&nbsp; quite&nbsp; limited&nbsp; in&nbsp; relation&nbsp; to&nbsp; what&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; or&nbsp; sk can&nbsp; use&nbsp; to&nbsp; maintain&nbsp; the same&nbsp; job ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; about&nbsp; dps since&nbsp; dps&nbsp; doesn't&nbsp; make&nbsp; any&nbsp; difference&nbsp; toward&nbsp; actual&nbsp; aggro .<FONT color=#ffff00>&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>1. Outside of Crypt of Decay, there are very few undead in this game for level 60+ zones.&nbsp; Very few.&nbsp; GoD has extremely few undead until you get into the back zones.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>2.&nbsp; The paladin forums have all shown from massive amounts of parsing that with Slay Undead 3, on average paladin DPS fails to exceed warrior DPS, even on undead.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>3.&nbsp; The original message hit on the&nbsp;issue that warrior weapons do not match up against knight weapons.&nbsp; While "itemization" may certainly be&nbsp;a legitimate gripe for warriors, in that the variety of good warrior weapons isn't very large, to compare the knight weapons to warrior weapons based strictly on stats... is like hiding important information.&nbsp; And that important information is that comparing stats (eg. damage/delay) fails to cover the reality that knights cannot dual wield, and thus cannot maintain 80% of warrior DPS if the damage/delay isn't skewed.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>---------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Being able to solo with or without buffs is going way off target for the discussion.&nbsp; At higher levels (60+) very few classes can solo, and of the ones that can solo, all of them are caster classes, so it's irrelevent for discussions of knight vs. warrior disparities.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></FONT>
<DIV>the&nbsp; ability&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo&nbsp; for&nbsp; exp&nbsp; is&nbsp; totally&nbsp; relevant&nbsp; under&nbsp; every&nbsp; circumstance .&nbsp; only&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; and&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; cannot&nbsp; solo&nbsp; effectively&nbsp; somewhere&nbsp;&nbsp; post&nbsp; level&nbsp; 65&nbsp; . how&nbsp; much&nbsp; exp&nbsp; do&nbsp; you&nbsp; get while&nbsp; lfg&nbsp; ?&nbsp;&nbsp; how&nbsp; much&nbsp; can someone&nbsp; who&nbsp; can&nbsp; solo&nbsp; ?</DIV></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Only warrior and cleric cannot solo effectively?&nbsp; I imagine the rogues would disagree with you, as well as the paladins.&nbsp; If we focus on the word "effectively", then several other classes might be added to the list of "cannot solo."</FONT></DIV></DIV></DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>In reality, no class solos in a meaningful way.&nbsp; The amount of effort to solo post -60 is profound.&nbsp; Caster classes can do it significantly easier than melee classes, but even then the amount of mana expended means significant downtime for meditation afterwards.&nbsp; Yes, there are *always* exceptions to this, but even then the exceptions are routinely among the casters... where buffing issues are not as important.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT><FONT color=#ffff00>How much exp do i get while LFG?&nbsp; None.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>How much exp do I get when soloing?&nbsp; About 4-8% AA exp every&nbsp;60 minutes if I win&nbsp;the fights, which is rather rare.&nbsp; One death = about 0.5% exp lost (after self-rez0 and a 30 minute CR usually.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>How much exp do I get in an exp group?&nbsp; About 120% AA exp every 60 minutes in EP level zones.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>The difference between grouping and soloing is so profound that I no longer even bother trying to solo unless I'm doing boring quest things.</FONT></P>
<P>
<HR>
</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
																		
