			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 164 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='2 ratings - 3.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>The problem is that knights don't have a voidance disc.&nbsp; Thus, rangers, beastlords, berserkers, warriors, monks, rogues, and even bards survive, but paladins and shadow knights do not.&nbsp; So despite wearing plate armor, the knights die just like int casters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>then&nbsp; maybe instead of&nbsp; trying&nbsp; to&nbsp; do&nbsp; everything&nbsp; ,&nbsp; you&nbsp; should be&nbsp; doing&nbsp; WHAT&nbsp;&nbsp; you&nbsp; are&nbsp; good&nbsp; at&nbsp; ,,&nbsp; oh&nbsp; wait&nbsp; ,&nbsp; you are a pally&nbsp; . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>sk's&nbsp; in&nbsp; general&nbsp; don't&nbsp; have a problem&nbsp; of&nbsp; doing&nbsp; what&nbsp; is&nbsp; best&nbsp; for&nbsp; a&nbsp; raid ,&nbsp; instead of&nbsp; whats&nbsp; best&nbsp; for&nbsp; personal&nbsp; glory&nbsp; . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>1. Outside of Crypt of Decay, there are very few undead in this game for level 60+ zones.&nbsp; Very few.&nbsp; GoD has extremely few undead until you get into the back zones.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>crypts&nbsp; in&nbsp; HoH&nbsp; ,&nbsp; most&nbsp; of&nbsp; the&nbsp; early&nbsp; oow&nbsp; instanced&nbsp; zones ,&nbsp; MM&nbsp; ldon's&nbsp; have&nbsp; no&nbsp; actual&nbsp; value&nbsp; then&nbsp; .&nbsp; name&nbsp; me a&nbsp; mob&nbsp; that&nbsp; a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; gets&nbsp; that&nbsp; kind&nbsp; of&nbsp; possible&nbsp; dps&nbsp; from&nbsp; ? btw ,&nbsp; named&nbsp; in&nbsp; akheva&nbsp; are&nbsp; undead , and&nbsp; named in&nbsp; ssra&nbsp; for&nbsp; the most&nbsp; part&nbsp; except&nbsp; emp . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>2.&nbsp; The paladin forums have all shown from massive amounts of parsing that with Slay Undead 3, on average paladin DPS fails to exceed warrior DPS, even on undead.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>note&nbsp; that&nbsp; average&nbsp; dps&nbsp; vs&nbsp; actual&nbsp; dps&nbsp; are&nbsp; 2&nbsp; different things .&nbsp; actual&nbsp; dps&nbsp; of&nbsp; tanking&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; is&nbsp; 45 %&nbsp; lower&nbsp; than&nbsp; actual&nbsp; parsing&nbsp; you&nbsp; have&nbsp; done&nbsp; (&nbsp; assuming&nbsp; they&nbsp; are&nbsp; defensive or&nbsp; evasive )&nbsp; so&nbsp; that&nbsp; will need&nbsp; to&nbsp; be taken&nbsp; into&nbsp; account&nbsp; since thats the&nbsp; situation&nbsp; we&nbsp; are&nbsp; talking&nbsp; about .&nbsp; if on the other&nbsp; hand&nbsp; we&nbsp; are&nbsp; talking&nbsp; about&nbsp; NON tanking&nbsp; situations ,&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; don't&nbsp; need&nbsp; the&nbsp; hp&nbsp; or aggro&nbsp; capabilities&nbsp; they&nbsp; have .&nbsp; since&nbsp; that&nbsp; would&nbsp; be a&nbsp; pure&nbsp; dps&nbsp; situation&nbsp; you&nbsp; (palidan&nbsp; )&nbsp; should&nbsp; be&nbsp; using a&nbsp; 2&nbsp; hander&nbsp; rendering this&nbsp; discussion on&nbsp; 1&nbsp; handed&nbsp; wepon&nbsp; availability&nbsp; moot&nbsp; . </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>3.&nbsp; The original message hit on the&nbsp;issue that warrior weapons do not match up against knight weapons.&nbsp; While "itemization" may certainly be&nbsp;a legitimate gripe for warriors, in that the variety of good warrior weapons isn't very large, to compare the knight weapons to warrior weapons based strictly on stats... is like hiding important information.&nbsp; And that important information is that comparing stats (eg. damage/delay) fails to cover the reality that knights cannot dual wield, and thus cannot maintain 80% of warrior DPS if the damage/delay isn't skewed</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>the&nbsp; original&nbsp; message&nbsp; refers&nbsp; to&nbsp; choice&nbsp; of&nbsp; availability&nbsp; of&nbsp; weapons&nbsp; for&nbsp; situation.&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; to&nbsp; maintain&nbsp; aggro&nbsp; have a&nbsp; severly&nbsp; limited&nbsp; selection&nbsp; of&nbsp; weapons&nbsp; available whereas&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; can&nbsp; use&nbsp; any&nbsp; crap&nbsp; and&nbsp; hold&nbsp; aggro&nbsp; via&nbsp; spells . if&nbsp; you are&nbsp; comparing&nbsp; knight&nbsp; only&nbsp; weaps&nbsp; vs&nbsp; any&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; only&nbsp; weap&nbsp; , than&nbsp;&nbsp; you&nbsp; really&nbsp; need&nbsp; to&nbsp; get&nbsp; a&nbsp; clue . warrior only&nbsp; weapons&nbsp; fall&nbsp; well&nbsp; short&nbsp; of&nbsp; any&nbsp; knight&nbsp; only&nbsp; weap .&nbsp; the&nbsp; only&nbsp; 2&nbsp; weaps a&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; can&nbsp; use&nbsp; that&nbsp; approximates&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; stats&nbsp; is&nbsp; a&nbsp; blade&nbsp; of&nbsp; war&nbsp; and&nbsp; darkblade&nbsp; of&nbsp; zek&nbsp; .&nbsp; both&nbsp; of&nbsp; which&nbsp; knights&nbsp; can&nbsp; use .&nbsp; if&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; cannot&nbsp; maintain&nbsp; dps&nbsp; because of&nbsp; skill caps&nbsp; that&nbsp; probably is in&nbsp; the&nbsp; sony&nbsp; vision&nbsp; and&nbsp; should&nbsp; be&nbsp; addressed&nbsp; in&nbsp; the PALIDAN&nbsp;&nbsp; forum ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; here .&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>
<P><FONT color=#ffff00>In reality, no class solos in a meaningful way.&nbsp; The amount of effort to solo post -60 is profound.&nbsp; Caster classes can do it significantly easier than melee classes, but even then the amount of mana expended means significant downtime for meditation afterwards.&nbsp; Yes, there are *always* exceptions to this, but even then the exceptions are routinely among the casters... where buffing issues are not as important.</FONT></P>
<P>necro&nbsp; and&nbsp; druid&nbsp; grow&nbsp; up&nbsp; soloing ,&nbsp; you&nbsp; can&nbsp; solo&nbsp; a&nbsp; necro&nbsp; bl&nbsp; or&nbsp; druid&nbsp; to&nbsp; 65&nbsp; without&nbsp;&nbsp; ever&nbsp; grouping . sk's&nbsp; can&nbsp; solo&nbsp;&nbsp; post&nbsp; 62&nbsp; or&nbsp; so&nbsp; quite&nbsp; effectively&nbsp; in&nbsp; PoV&nbsp; ,&nbsp; monks&nbsp; solo&nbsp; from&nbsp; 50 - 60&nbsp; in&nbsp; sol&nbsp; b .&nbsp; even&nbsp; rogues&nbsp; can&nbsp; pick&nbsp; up&nbsp; exp&nbsp; in&nbsp; droga&nbsp; post&nbsp;&nbsp; 65&nbsp; with the right&nbsp; aa's&nbsp; .&nbsp; palidan&nbsp;&nbsp; solo&nbsp; in&nbsp; ssra ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; HoH&nbsp; on my&nbsp; server&nbsp; ,&nbsp; rangers&nbsp; bowkite&nbsp; aa's&nbsp; in&nbsp; fire , is&nbsp; it&nbsp; meaning&nbsp; full ? they&nbsp; all&nbsp; have the&nbsp; ABILITY&nbsp;&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo for&nbsp; exp . warrior&nbsp; and&nbsp; cleric&nbsp; in general&nbsp; do&nbsp; not&nbsp; . EVER&nbsp; . cleric&nbsp; can&nbsp; create&nbsp; groups ,&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; are kind of&nbsp; stuck&nbsp; ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; enough dps&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; enough&nbsp; mitigation&nbsp; to&nbsp; not&nbsp; die&nbsp; ,&nbsp; no healing&nbsp; ability&nbsp; or movement&nbsp; modification&nbsp; to&nbsp; escape . </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV></DIV></DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
