									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 159 times<br>
									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_3.gif' border=0 alt='2 ratings - 3.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>It would be far more significant if the paladin had the same HP and AC as you while wearing the same equipment that you are wearing.&nbsp; But the fact is, they are not getting the same HP/AC.&nbsp; That paladin personal buff can definitely make up some ground, but I would bet it would still leave them a good 500-800 HP behind you.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>your&nbsp; right&nbsp; ,&nbsp;&nbsp; THEY&nbsp; ARE GETTING MORE&nbsp; .&nbsp; because&nbsp; we&nbsp; are&nbsp; all&nbsp; wearing&nbsp; identical&nbsp; gear&nbsp; , and&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; can&nbsp; get&nbsp; aa&nbsp; considerably&nbsp; faster&nbsp; (&nbsp; ability&nbsp; to&nbsp; solo )&nbsp; and they have&nbsp; a&nbsp; personal&nbsp; buff&nbsp; i&nbsp;&nbsp;cannot &nbsp; get&nbsp; .&nbsp; almost&nbsp; every&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; in&nbsp; guild&nbsp; have&nbsp; 4-600&nbsp; more&nbsp; hp&nbsp; ,&nbsp; and&nbsp; 50&nbsp; -&nbsp; 70&nbsp; ac&nbsp; .&nbsp; now&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; assume&nbsp; i'm&nbsp; a&nbsp; 12000&nbsp; hp warrior in&nbsp; full&nbsp; time&nbsp; gear&nbsp; ,&nbsp; (palidan&nbsp; can&nbsp; max&nbsp; out&nbsp; around&nbsp; 11400&nbsp; hp&nbsp;&nbsp; buffed&nbsp; in&nbsp; time&nbsp; gear)&nbsp; a&nbsp; 10&nbsp; %&nbsp;&nbsp; bonus&nbsp; in&nbsp; gear&nbsp;&nbsp; turns&nbsp; a&nbsp; 12000&nbsp; hp warrior into&nbsp; a&nbsp; 12900&nbsp; hp&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; which&nbsp; still isn't&nbsp; significant&nbsp; when a mob&nbsp; quads&nbsp; and&nbsp; hits&nbsp; for&nbsp; 3000 .&nbsp; on the other&nbsp; hand&nbsp; ,&nbsp;&nbsp; your&nbsp; totally&nbsp; fearless&nbsp; aa&nbsp; is&nbsp; much&nbsp; more&nbsp; usefull&nbsp; than&nbsp; my&nbsp; fear&nbsp; resistant&nbsp; aa , and&nbsp; warcry aa at&nbsp; 1/4&nbsp;&nbsp; the&nbsp; cost&nbsp; of the warrior&nbsp; aa .&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Once the LEVEL cap is reached (level 70 with OoW), then exp penalties for race become moot.&nbsp; Thus, even tho you may not be advocating ogres and trolls as the only raid&nbsp;tanks,&nbsp;the&nbsp;ogre and troll initial&nbsp;statistical advantage with regard to strength and stamina would give them a profound advantage if it were to extend to level 70 toons.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Honestly, who do you look at for being the boss mob tank; the ogre warrior with 355 strength and 360 stamina who now has 12,000 hp thanks to the stamina cap boost, or do you look at the gnome warrior with 295 strength and 305 stamina who can only get up to 11,000 HP because of their racial differences?</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Removal of the stat caps creates a measurable difference that provides an advantage to some races.&nbsp; When that happens the amount of "differences" you see will actually decrease because people will gravitate to the races with the advantages.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>There's a reason you see so few dark elf warriors.&nbsp; There's a reason you see so few gnome warriors.&nbsp; There's a reason you see so few erudite or gnome clerics, but tons of high elf clerics.&nbsp; There's a reason you see so many erudite and gnomish int casters.&nbsp; </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Remove the stat caps and just about all your raid tanks will be ogres and trolls.&nbsp; It's just how it works.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>..............................................................................................................................................................................................................</DIV>
<DIV>i'm&nbsp; an&nbsp; ogre ,&nbsp; yup&nbsp; its&nbsp; true .&nbsp; will i&nbsp; be&nbsp; tanking&nbsp; our&nbsp; raid&nbsp; encounters ?&nbsp; i&nbsp; don't&nbsp; normally&nbsp; tank&nbsp; now ,&nbsp; why&nbsp; would&nbsp; i&nbsp; start then&nbsp; ?becausse i&nbsp; have&nbsp; 300&nbsp; or&nbsp; 600&nbsp; or&nbsp; 1000&nbsp; more&nbsp; hp ?&nbsp; nope .&nbsp; being a raid&nbsp; warrior is&nbsp; much more than&nbsp; you&nbsp; must&nbsp; believe . in&nbsp; general&nbsp; your&nbsp; main&nbsp; tank on&nbsp; a&nbsp; raid&nbsp; is&nbsp; your&nbsp; slowest&nbsp;&nbsp; draw&nbsp; tank&nbsp; .&nbsp; it&nbsp; doesn't&nbsp; matter&nbsp; if&nbsp; you have&nbsp; 8000&nbsp; hp&nbsp; or&nbsp; 9000&nbsp; hp&nbsp; when&nbsp; you get&nbsp; 1&nbsp; rounded .&nbsp; it&nbsp; doesn't&nbsp; matter&nbsp; if&nbsp; you have&nbsp; no&nbsp; magic&nbsp; resist&nbsp; or&nbsp; poison&nbsp; resist&nbsp; or&nbsp; fire resist&nbsp; when&nbsp; you are&nbsp; being healed&nbsp; every&nbsp; 2&nbsp; seconds .&nbsp; palidan&nbsp; will&nbsp; still&nbsp; tank&nbsp; the&nbsp; encounters that&nbsp; root&nbsp; and memblur .&nbsp; warriors&nbsp; will&nbsp; still&nbsp; tank&nbsp; the&nbsp; high&nbsp; dps&nbsp; mobs . perpetual&nbsp; defensive&nbsp; team&nbsp; tanking&nbsp; will&nbsp; continue&nbsp; no&nbsp; matter&nbsp; where this&nbsp; discussion&nbsp; goes .&nbsp; removing the&nbsp; cap&nbsp; won't&nbsp; change&nbsp; who is&nbsp; available&nbsp; to&nbsp; raid . if&nbsp; you lead&nbsp; raids&nbsp; (&nbsp; and i&nbsp; do )&nbsp; you&nbsp; dictate&nbsp; who&nbsp; is&nbsp; best&nbsp; suited&nbsp; toward&nbsp; their&nbsp; role&nbsp; on the raid&nbsp; no&nbsp; matter&nbsp; what&nbsp; class&nbsp; or&nbsp; race&nbsp; .&nbsp; its the player&nbsp; that&nbsp; makes&nbsp; the character&nbsp; ,&nbsp; not&nbsp; some&nbsp; stat&nbsp; .&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>recently&nbsp; we&nbsp; have&nbsp; used&nbsp; a&nbsp; necro&nbsp; to&nbsp; kite&nbsp; CC&nbsp;.&nbsp; pally&nbsp; main&nbsp; tanks ,&nbsp; beastlords&nbsp; slow .&nbsp; warrior&nbsp; range&nbsp; dps .&nbsp; ranger&nbsp; pull&nbsp; teams ,</DIV>
<DIV>its&nbsp; all&nbsp; about&nbsp; adapting&nbsp; what&nbsp; you have&nbsp; available&nbsp; on&nbsp; a&nbsp; raid&nbsp; to&nbsp; get the&nbsp; job&nbsp; done .&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; cannot&nbsp; adapt&nbsp; your&nbsp; thinking&nbsp; to&nbsp; fit the&nbsp; people&nbsp; you have&nbsp; available&nbsp; you&nbsp; are&nbsp; always&nbsp; going&nbsp; to&nbsp; be bound&nbsp; to&nbsp; fail .&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>even&nbsp; your&nbsp; success&nbsp; will&nbsp; be&nbsp; failures&nbsp; if&nbsp; you&nbsp; are&nbsp; unwilling&nbsp; to&nbsp; adapt&nbsp; . &nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></FONT></DIV>
																		
